@jinhyukchang Thanks for testing the extractor so thoroughly. Sorry for not responding earlier, but for some reason, I'm having build problems locally when I try to run the tests. I'm ready to take a look at the issue you raised with the sample number query. So it seems you are pulling using `source.querybased.query` is that correct? What is the query you are using?

Hi @bjvanov ,
Yes, I was using source.querybased.query and here's SQL query commented above.

SELECT ORDER_ID, DATE_PLACED, GG_MODI_TS FROM ORDERS2 WHERE ROWNUM <= 10000

If you look at the log in previous comment, it changes it to 
SELECT COUNT(1) FROM (SELECT rownum <= 10000 1 as col FROM ORDERS2 where (1=1))temp
and throws out exception.

I didn't go through the code to pin point the cause but I was using this query on my testing and you can also take a look at my PR if it helps trouble shooting. I tried to add other where clause into query but didn't have any problem so I guess the problem is limited to this case.
Could you explain "2. changed DEFAULT_USE_ALL_OBJECTS from true to false" ?
replaced with https://github.com/linkedin/gobblin/pull/1128
with DEFAULT_USE_ALL_OBJECTS set to true, the single salesforce  job will pull all the data
